    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for the Austin Waves is anchored by three primary assets who possess the ideal confluence of order placement and pitcher-matchup vulnerabilities. **Jackson Merrill** (75.11) represents our strongest play of the day; facing Sean Burke, **Merrill** benefits from a massive 13% boost due to his platoon advantage and an 87% stolen base probability against Burke\u2019s slow delivery, making him a primary target for speed and counting stats. **Kyle Tucker** (70.51) and **Jacob Wilson** (68.37) follow closely behind. **Tucker** is poised to exploit the 4.48 xERA of Michael McGreevy, while **Wilson** receives a substantial boost from batting leadoff against the vulnerable Slade Cecconi. While **Drake Baldwin** (66.86) remains a high-scoring catcher option, his value is predicated on his assumed #2 spot in the order, which remains subject to the final lineup posting.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Coby Mayo**, who yielded a respectable 49.90 but ultimately fell behind the positional utility of **Nasim Nunez** and **Josh Jung**. While **Mayo** benefits from the stolen base potential inherent in facing Ryan Weathers\u2019 deliberate pace on the mound, his projected #8 spot in the order severely hampered his efficiency score, pushing him behind the higher-upside opportunities offered by **Andy Pages** (60.24) and **Josh Jung** (59.57). We are monitoring the status of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (60.85) closely; despite his strong profile, he faces a tough matchup against Connor Prielipp (3.34 xERA), and his performance will be the primary barometer for our run production today.\n\nStrategic risks remain tied to the \"Lineup Pending\" designations across the roster. **Gunnar Henderson** (57.16) is a notable concern; while his leadoff status provides a floor, his efficiency is currently hampered by a 15% penalty due to the platoon disadvantage against Ryan Weathers. We are banking on **Henderson**\u2019s elite speed and Weathers\u2019 slow delivery to offset these negative splits. If the confirmed lineups shift our current assumed spots for **Dominic Smith** or **Liam Hicks**, we will be forced to re-evaluate the utility of our bench depth, specifically looking to integrate the high-contact profile of **Miguel Vargas** if the right pinch-hit opportunity arises.",
